sub_title: Passionate about improving life through science
summary: I have several years of experience analysing complex scientific and regulatory data to provide key insights and strategic advice to stakeholders and decision makers. My background includes vaccinology, immunology, and biomedical sciences, and I am proficient in generating scientific publications, reports, visuals, and presentations. I enjoy being in a challenging role where I can use my scientific knowledge for problem-solving and expand my skillset. One of my proudest achievements has been my contribution to New Zealand's COVID-19 response - where I delivered scientific advice and helped shape policy throughout the pandemic - starting from vaccine procurement and working through the rollout. I have an interest in drug and vaccine development, including regulatory affairs towards licensure. I'm always looking to expand my knowledge within the pharmaceutical sector.
